<br>
Problems-Could not do Pandos because i was KOS to him too.<br>
<br>
    What I did, kill orcs in crushbone for about 10 years(50+hours it seemed like pling all the noobs in the zone with es bp  and all the other buffs while i wasted my time) til i was ally with just about everyone but Faydark Champions. Well after killing even MORE orcs I finally got to Kindly with Faydark Champions. So i was able to do the coin part. Then I headed off to EK to get the reaver. Guess what, KOS to Althele. Well, invis trick works on this so its no problem got this done so far. <br>
<br>
    Then i headed off to TD to talk to Aldrik and hes indiff and wont talk to me. So off to S. Felwith to do Batwing quest. Fortunately I am not kos to Keepers of the Art so i was able to do this. The things I noticed are the faction hits I was getting while doing this lil quest. Keepers of the art, Faydark Champions and King Tearix Tex(sp). Well, I wish I would of known this off the start and would of done this instead of commiting Genocide in Crushbone. Faydark Champions is the faction Telin is in btw.  Another thing i noticed is the King Tearix Tex(sp) faction. On a hunch I decided to check out old Pandos to see if I was still KOS to him, since kiling orcs didnt raise my faction with him anyhow I decided to give this a shot. Well sure enough Pandos is in King Tearix tex(sp) faction. <br>
<br>
So basically if you havent screwed yourself with keepers of the Arts, you can get back most of the factions back by doing the batwing quest to A-get your faydark champions and King T faction up til the point you are no longer kos to Pandos, then do Pandos Muffin quest to get all the other factions up as well, Clerics of tunare, soldiers of tunare, Faydark Champions and King T.<br>
<br>
So basically I did alot of leg work that I could of bypassed If i would of tried this first but, I didnt know what faction Pandos was on and I was darn lucky i was not kos to Keepers of the arts to be able to do batwng quest. <br>
<br>
Only hitch is I think Felwithe guards are on Stormguard faction but not sure, but you should be able to invis past all that and to the room the npc is in to turn in the batwings without a problem seeing as she is alone in the room.<br>
<br>
Good luck.<br>
